      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY SOMETHING (1) missed the frame and safely held latest finishing 8th at The Gardens following on from a win (23.06) at this track the start prior. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Looks the one to beat on her best form. HEY MAC (2) was well fancied but drifted back before winding up with a late dash home to place, a neck from the winner (16.10) at The Gardens in Grade 5. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Well placed and gets her chance. IMOGENE PASS (8) was a last-start winner from the inside at Taree Super Track over 300m (17.53) after charging straight to the lead, scoring by 0.8 lengths. Must include in calculations. PITMAN GO WELL (4) recorded a one length win (22.42) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. Already a winner from this draw.",
